Homer's the Captain of Apollo's race,</br>Renowned Virgil claims the second place:</br>Spenser our glory 'tis thy golden pen</br>Admits the third before all other men.</br>Sage Homer, Virgil, Spenser laureat</br>Made a poeticall Triumvirat.</br>Greece, Rome, and England chaleng to your merits</br>T' have nurst the bravest Heliconian spirits.</br>Only King David's Muse, Jehova's birth,</br>Excells as much as Heaven excells the earth.
So conceives the Autor, J. H.

Apollinaris dux Homeris est Chori:</br>Teneas secundum Virgili merito locum:</br>Spensere Lautiger, Maro, Maeonides Senex</br>Vos fama celebret tres viros Phoebi sacros.</br>Pelasga terra, Roma, dulcis Anglia</br>Tres nutricastis optimos vates gregis,</br>Solum Davidis Musa, de Caelo fata</br>Superato, Coelum ut superat has terrae plagas.
